annotation.TEXT: Ow. Didn't hit down on that slope in time.
And now to get all the Yoshi coins in this level...
Alright, so now King Koopa's castle is unlocked! So, should I head there next?
I think maybe I should go in this pipe. What do you guys think?
And now for the rest...
Hahaha, I don't think I've ever stomped Ludwig quite like that before!

1 vote for me to find out what Secret-3's level music is (I haven't found it yet...), 1 vote for the castle hidden under Youkai Mountain, 1 vote to have Mario explore the Mushroom World in search of the ancient 4 colored Yoshi artifacts and unlock a mystical gateway to the lost (insert species here) civilization, 1 vote to play both 7-Castle and Secret-4 at the same time using two emulators, 1 vote to head to Ice World for a few days, lose my sanity, then cook and eat Yoshi out of boredom, 1 vote for a PSA on Yoshi sacrifice starring Chiyo-Chan from Azumanga Daioh, 1 vote for me to play as Metal Mario, 1 vote for Star-4-1, 4 votes for 7-Castle, and 7 votes for Secret-4! Alrighty then, Secret-4 it is!

Well, that's done. Also, I don't think this boss room was edited in any way. Weren't all of the other Koopalings made slightly more difficult with either an extra podoboo or a bullet generator or something? But, I didn't see any additions here...
I think I'll stick with my two feathers for now.
Okay, so we've got some gold Bowser statues... Is this level going to be statue-themed?
It's a cape and a 1-up, both of which are meaningless to me right now.
Convection, schmonvection.
Oh, crap! I totally botched that jump! Now, I'm probably doomed!
Try not to get crushed!
Okay, so we've reached the top, but did I miss anything to the left?
Wow, holy banana, did I get lucky back there then! (Maybe I should buy a Mega Millions lottery ticket now?) However, I don't think that's very fair level design...
Oh, no. This is definitely not statue-themed. (Well, I don't know that for sure yet...)
Midpoint! And let me guess, the wind blows the other way during the second half, right?
A whole bunch of somethings.
Oh, good. I was hoping to see midpoint here. I need the power up.
To be continued... However, there's one thing I want to check now...
There is something to the right, but I'm not reaching it from this side. Better approach from above.
If I hit this block once and only once, where do I end up?
Nuts... Oh, wait! I stomped him, somehow!
...Or, maybe not. I seem to be okay, and this path leads to a Yoshi coin. Maybe the switches just affect whether I can get bonuses?
Aw, nuts. Looks like I did need the flower after all, in order to reach that Yoshi coin.
Or, should I head to Secret-5 next? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
Alright, so we're going down now, and thankfully, I don't see any lava or line-guided platforms anywhere.
Okay, got 'em all, and I'm outta here. I'm not going to bother finishing the level again this time.
More switch block assistance FTW! Too bad I wasn't caped, or I could've gotten capes there.
Don't need nearly as much runway to take off if the wind is blowing against me.
Maybe I shouldn't glide so much. These jumps were most likely meant for a non-caped hero, so gliding might get me in trouble.
Or punctured!
Alright, here's the one I couldn't get before.
Alright, now before I do anything else...
Yes, I'll happily take the mushroom this time!
Alright, a feather! I needed that!
...I've decided to play the castle next!
Plenty of other hazards, but at least I've got switch palace blocks helping me out. Also, I wonder if I missed a Yoshi coin in the first half...
Do the Chucks really have to practice their sports in such harsh weather?
I assume this leads to the goal...
What the... Well, that's a weird glitch! Looks like the wind pushes you while you're screen scrolling, and can push you through walls!
I'm pretty sure I want that in the OFF position... I think...
Yep, there's the goal, along with another Chuck doing sports practice. Well, at least it isn't snowing anymore.
Argh! I've gotta stop screwing up my jumps! Also, that lava has been getting uncomfortably close to me...
Oh, yeah. It's blowing to the right now. Also, there's a flower here, but I'm not going to grab it right now.
Huh. Doesn't look like that happens every time, though. But still, that's weird, and I'm sure it would be deadly if you screen scrolled in a poor spot!
Argh! Well, that was stupid of me. I jumped right into that guy. Sorry, Yoshi...
Yeah, I'm guessing the ON position would've dumped me in the lava... maybe.
Time for yet another bonus game. Yay.
Now, it'll be very helpful if I don't let him jump off the side of the screen.
Okay, that's better. I'm not going to go get another Yoshi right now though, because...
Well, I've located all of the Yoshi coins, but I'm going to need to make another trip through the level to get the one I couldn't reach earlier.
And, I guess it's Ludwig. Too bad I don't have a flower to take him out in two seconds with, but let's see if I can defeat him with just one flight...
Hey, it's the last Yoshi coin, so I guess I didn't miss any (unless there were more than five in the level).
It's a blizza-MOOOOOONNN!!! GIMME GIMME GIMME! YES!!!
(No votes against the YT staff or new channel design this time?)
Yeah, whatever.
Welcome to another episode of Super SIG World 21! The voting results this time are as follows:
Okay, that was kind of cool, and I really wasn't expecting to be able to dive bomb there!
Oh, man. I gotta hit ON/OFF blocks, too? Well, this could get very tricky!
Mushroom. No thanks.
Well, I'll just hit every switch I come across if I can, and see where I end up. Then, I'll repeat the level if I missed any Yoshi coins.
And now, we're in Roto-Disc city apparently...
Really? It just dumps you into the lava?!
I'm gonna need this flower, obviously.
Doesn't look like there's anything over there...
Time for yet another failure. D'oh.
Gulp! Huh, it doesn't feel like the wind affects me as much if I'm not fighting it, but maybe that's just me.
(Cough) Ahem... As I was saying, it's a blizzard level, and it appears to be blowing me backwards. Also, we've got DKC2 ice level music, which is nice.
Well, this zigzag seems easy enough...
It's time for Mario to do some punting practice of his own...
And, I guess it's boss time!

Ooh, good thing I learned that purple buzzies are slide-killable! Unfortunately, I seem to have momentarily forgotten how to dodge a fireball... However, my reserve feather has pushed me beyond the 2 million point mark!
Good thing the bubbling part of the lava is not harmful. Still, shouldn't Mario's shoes have burned up by now?
Luigifan22222's translation: "I unfolded many weapons fierce battles and finally beat last Koopaling, Ludwig. The castle of Bowser is already the very front. OK, shall we go defeat it as usual?"
